Types of relations in Java Class
==================================

In java we can use below 2 types of relations 
1. IS-A relation ----> inheritance
2. HAS-A relation ---> Composition


       |---Person   
user ->|---student
       |---Employee

what ever the propertis for "user" , all are applicable for Person,Student, Employee
Student IS-A User
Person  IS-A User
Employee IS-A User

--> If one class wants to re-use all the properties of another class then we will go for IS-A relation.

Inheritance is a good example for this .

========
Example:
========
package Polymorphism;

class user{
	
	int id;
	String name;
	
	void m1() {
		
		System.out.println("My id is :"+id+", My name is :"+ name);
	}
}
public class IsAhasArelationship extends user {
	
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		
		IsAhasArelationship s = new IsAhasArelationship();
		s.id=100;
		s.name="Ashol";
		s.m1();
				
	}

}

