HAS-A relation
==============

--> If one class wants to re-use some properties of another class then we will go for HAS-A relation.

              CAR --- ENGINE

here, CAR has functionaly and ENGINE has a functionality

So, CAR has a relationship with ENGINE

Example : Composition is the exmaple for this .
=========
Example:
=========

package Polymorphism;

class Engine{
	
	int id;
	String name;
	String Fueltype;
	
	void start() {
		
		System.out.println("Engine starting......");
	}
	
	
}
public class HasARelationship  {
	void drive() {
		
		Engine e = new Engine();//HAS A relation
		e.start();
		System.out.println("My journey started....");

    }
	public static void main(String [] args) {
		
		HasARelationship c = new HasARelationship();
		c.drive();
		System.out.println();
	}

}
