ABSTRACTION:
============

->The process of hiding un-necessary  data and providing only useful data is called Abstraction.
-> We can achieve abstraction using interfaces and Abstract classes.
===========
Interface
==========

-> Interface are used to achieve loosely coupling and abstraction.
-> Interfaces contains only abstract method.(upto 1.7v of java)
->To create a interface we will use "interface " keyword.
-> Interface does not contains "constructor".
-> We can not create object for the interface.
-> Once interface is created then anybody can provide implementation for the interface.
-> Implementing interface means overriding "interface abstract methods"
-> When we are implementing a interface then its mandatory to implement all abstract methods of that interface.
->To implement a interface , we will use "implements " keyword.
-> One java class can implement multiple interfaces at a time.
-> One java class can extend properties from only one class and it can implement multiple interfaces at a time.

example:

        ---->KOTAK
RBI     ----> SBI 
        ---->AXIS
